main event: A UFO sighting was reported in Sutersville, Pennsylvania on June 5, 1965, describing a round, silver object with three small antennas that glowed and was assumed to be a balloon.
interesting points: The object was visible for about 20 minutes and was observed hovering in the sky., An instrument was used but could not determine the exact altitude of the object., The sighting was initially considered to potentially be a satellite., The object's trajectory was towards the northwest., The document is part of Project Blue Book and contains multiple redactions.
sighted object: a round, silver object with three small antennas
witness description: civilian who observed the object visually
